    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a potent offensive profile, anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (85.72) and **Gunnar Henderson** (83.18). **Kyle Tucker** is our premier play, benefiting from a soft matchup against Feltner and a park environment that juices his base projection significantly. Similarly, **Gunnar Henderson** stands out despite the 31% rain risk in his contest; his leadoff role and platoon advantage against Williams, G. remain statistically dominant. We are also capitalizing on the high-upside matchup against Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1rquez, which elevates **Nolan Schanuel** (67.16) and **Josh Lowe** (72.21) into \"Strong\" start territory. **Josh Lowe** is particularly enticing today, as M\u00e1rquez\u2019s slow delivery offers a rare steal opportunity that aligns perfectly with our need to aggressively pursue stolen bases.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved keeping **Nasim Nunez** (60.21) on the bench. While his speed and platoon versatility are assets, his lower raw efficiency score relative to the rest of the infield forced him out of the starting nine. The optimizer prioritized the pure hitting profile of **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56) and the favorable park and matchup factors boosting **Jacob Wilson** (70.28). While **Luis Robert Jr.** (57.07) and **Jackson Merrill** (55.56) carry some risk due to platoon splits and, in **Jackson Merrill**'s case, a difficult opposing catcher's pop time, their baseline talent keeps them in the lineup over the surging **Nasim Nunez**. We will continue to monitor the statuses of **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Miguel Vargas**, who both maintain stable scoring floors (67.48 and 64.21 respectively) in their current roles. \n\nBeyond the weather concerns for **Gunnar Henderson** and **Coby Mayo**, we are cognizant that **Drake Baldwin** faces the toughest defensive test of the day against a refined pitcher in S\u00e1nchez, C, leading to his modest 48.67 score. We are betting on our middle-order depth\u2014specifically **Andy Pages** (73.82), whose 14% park factor boost makes him a high-efficiency pivot\u2014to mitigate any localized underperformance. We will keep a close eye on these \"Lineup Pending\" designations, as any deviation in batting order for **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** or **Nolan Schanuel** could trigger a late-afternoon recalibration of our 5x5 expectations.",
